text.tspan: Case study: Design of a performance measure
Instead of using binary success, the currently prevalent choice of performance measure,
we propose to use a few discrete performance levels with universal interpretation,
such as failed, weak, good, and excellent.
measures with just a few distinct values.
Result: The choice of performance measure matters. Different reasonable choices lead to very different measurements.
Binary success provides too little information
Using detailed observations hinders reuse, and
complicates the development of learning systems.
